From d98725f3ac2ff6b1fad52d7223275131e3692d08 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shriram K <shriram.k@arm.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Mar 2023 12:14:41 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 30/78] Platform/Sgi: Add initial support for RD-V3-Cfg1
 platform

Arm's RD-V3-Cfg1 platform is a variant of the RD-V3 platform.
Compared to RD-V3 platform, RD-V3-Cfg1 has a reduced core
count of eight Neoverse Poseidon CPUs and a smaller interconnect mesh.
As part of the initial platform support for RD-V3-Cfg1 platform,
add the corresponding ACPI tables, platform and flash description files.

Signed-off-by: Shriram K <shriram.k@arm.com>
Signed-off-by: Vivek Gautam <vivek.gautam@arm.com>
